EXTRACTED VALUE: Despite being just 26-years-old, Euro 2008 could represent his final farewell from the international fold.
The Swede returned home to join Gothenburg for a second time in July 2004 and has been an integral member of their side over the last four years.
The powerful forward enjoyed his best spell at Heerenveen scoring over 30 goals in his two seasons at the club.
He picked up another two FA Cup winners' medal in 2003 and 2005 as well another Premier League title in 2004.
Czech fans will hope the team can give the big guy a fitting send-off.
